Cotton futures were steady this morningon commission house buying. But trade selling was keeping gainsto a minimum, brokers said.    There was no news, but brokers said the market is technically weak and in search of a bottom. Recent news of poorexport sales remained a damper, brokers said.    Cotton for May delivery was up 0.25 cent at 56.05 cents alb in a 56.30 to 55.80 cent range.    December delivery was up 0.40 cent at 55.15 cents. Reuter&#3;